mol_012\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n      \"name\": \"PAH-to-phenylalanine branch feeding tyrosine network by shared aromatic precursor logic\",\n      \"description\": \"PAH photolysis yields phenylalanine and tyrosine together; in this network the phenylalanine-producing branch demonstrates convergence of aromatic precursor chemistry with tyrosine-producing chemistry through the same PAH source.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_013\", \"mol_011\", \"mol_012\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"name\": \"Surface Strecker route seeded by hydrothermal H2-rich carbon fixation environment\",\n      \"description\": \"Hydrothermal reducing conditions establish carbon fixation and favorable amino-acid thermodynamics, while the actual aromatic aldehyde precursor is made by the Friedmann-Miller surface route and converted to tyrosine by Strecker chemistry.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_015\", \"rxn_001\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_009\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_018\", \"mol_007\", \"mol_010\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrothermal pyruvate-linked keto-acid tyrosine route\",\n      \"description\": \"Hydrothermal CO2 fixation to pyruvate establishes an alpha-keto-acid-rich setting that conceptually supports subsequent aromatic keto-acid chemistry; aromatic carbon comes from the phenol branch and final amination gives tyrosine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_012\", \"rxn_001\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_011\", \"rxn_013\", \"rxn_014\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_017\", \"mol_006\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_016\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"name\": \"Mixed atmospheric-hydrothermal complete route\",\n      \"description\": \"This integrative route begins with discharge generation of both acetylene and HCN, uses hydrothermal aromatic ring construction and hydrothermal Fe-rich functionalization to 4-HPA, and ends in surface Strecker synthesis of tyrosine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_011\", \"rxn_009\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_002\", \"mol_003\", \"mol_006\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_010\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"hub_molecules\": [\"mol_002\", \"mol_007\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_016\"],\n  \"convergence_points\": [\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_002\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_001\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_011\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_010\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_007\", \"rxn_011\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_009\", \"rxn_013\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_012\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\", \"rxn_014\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": []\n    }\n  ]\n}", "parsed_response": {"target_molecule": "Tyrosine", "overall_strategy": "This network follows the literature consensus that tyrosine is not formed in one pot from simple prebiotic feedstocks, but instead requires multi-environment assembly centered on aromatic precursors. The network therefore combines: (i) surface/high-energy generation of acetylene and HCN, (ii) mineral-catalyzed aromatic ring formation and hydroxylation to phenol or direct PAH input, (iii) hydrothermal Fe-rich clay/saponite-mediated Friedel-Crafts-type functionalization to 4-hydroxyphenylacetaldehyde or 4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate under thermodynamically favorable alkaline conditions, and (iv) Strecker or reductive amination/transamination steps to tyrosine. Direct tyrosine formation is only assigned where literature supports broad route classes; speculative bridging steps are explicitly labeled as such. Ten distinct pathways are provided by recombining the two literature-supported source classes for aromatic carbon (phenylacetylene/Friedmann-Miller and PAH/Chen-Bennu-Menez) with the t